description:
Commands currently use process.exit() for error handling instead of the Result<T> pattern defined in core/errors.

## Current Pattern (problematic)
```typescript
if (error) {
  ui.error('Something failed');
  process.exit(1);
}
```

## Desired Pattern
```typescript
async execute(options): Promise<Result<void>> {
  if (error) {
    return failure(new CommandError('Something failed'));
  }
  return success(void 0);
}
```

## Tasks
1. Refactor git/push to return Result<void>
2. Refactor git/pull to return Result<void>
3. Refactor git/commit to return Result<void>
4. Refactor git/branch to return Result<void>
5. Update CLI entry point to handle Result types
6. Integrate ErrorHandler with recovery strategies

## Benefits
- Better testability (no process.exit in tests)
- Composable error handling
- Consistent error reporting
- Enables retry/recovery strategies

Commands use Commander.js directly rather than the defined ICommand interface.

## Current Pattern
```typescript
export function createPushCommand(): Command {
  const command = new Command('push');
  command.description('...').action(async (options) => {...});
  return command;
}
```

## Desired Pattern
```typescript
export class PushCommand implements ICommand<GitPushOptions> {
  name = 'push';
  description = '...';

  async execute(options: GitPushOptions): Promise<Result<void>> {...}
  validate(options: unknown): options is GitPushOptions {...}
}
```

## Benefits
- Consistent command structure
- Better testability (mock execute)
- Type-safe options
- Enables command discovery
- Works with plugin system

## Tasks
1. Create CommandAdapter to bridge ICommand → Commander
2. Refactor git commands to implement ICommand
3. Refactor config commands
4. Refactor agent commands
5. Update command registration

The ContextDB class uses better-sqlite3 (synchronous) but wraps everything in async unnecessarily.

## Current Pattern (mixed)
```typescript
// Constructor is sync
constructor(dbPath: string) {
  this.db = new Database(dbPath);
  this.ready = this.initialize();
}

// Methods are async but using sync operations
async addContext(options): Promise<ContextItem> {
  await this.ensureReady();
  const stmt = this.db.prepare('...');  // sync!
  stmt.run(...);  // sync!
  return {...};
}
```

## Options
1. Keep async for future compatibility (e.g., switching to async DB)
2. Make sync since better-sqlite3 is sync
3. Use async factory pattern properly

## Recommended: Async Factory Pattern
```typescript
class ContextDB {
  private constructor(private db: Database) {}

  static async create(dbPath: string): Promise<ContextDB> {
    await mkdir(dirname(dbPath), { recursive: true });
    const db = new Database(dbPath);
    // Initialize schema
    return new ContextDB(db);
  }

  // Methods can be sync since DB is ready
  addContext(options: AddContextOptions): ContextItem {...}
}
```

## Tasks
1. Decide on sync vs async approach
2. Refactor initialization
3. Simplify method signatures
4. Update all callers
5. Add proper error handling
